The following repository has two subfolders:

V1 - Basic loader to execute a DLL payload (not reflective) 
V2 - Fully reflective loader designed for evasion purposes (in-memory execution), read the full paper to get into more technical details 

How to use it manually?

1. Upload or place the ASPX file in any IIS web root folder.

2. Access the page through your browser using: page.aspx?k=SECRET and configure the host-pinning. 

3. Upload or provide your payload in Base64 format and make sure to specify the exported function in the function export field.

4. Execute and wait.

an I use it with C2?

I released another tool called "PhantomLink" to perform that task. You can use it for lateral movement or host infection.
